    transliteration: "ātittaṉ, ampuli, aṅki, kupēraṉ, amarartaṅkōṉ\npōtiṟ piramaṉ, purāri, murāri, potiyamuṉi,\nkātip porupaṭaik kantaṉ, kaṇapati, kāmaṉ mutal\ncātitta puṇṇiyar eṇṇilar pōṟṟuvar taiyalaiyē.",
    meaning: "I am fine and She is fine; the silence placed in the Lord is fine; what She speaks and the trident She holds are fine; the matchless unique vine that is the Mother is fine—but is it right that I should stand at the door of the five senses and perish? O Mother, save me from this ruin!"
